cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and image processing, specifically material recognition for outdoor surfaces. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of this technology for autonomous agents, which suggests that it could also fall under cs.RO (Robotics and Control). The development of a novel approach for material recognition using a large dataset and neural network architecture also suggests that it could be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the creation of a material database, which could potentially fall under cs.GR (Graphics).
